  title: 題平陵驛亭
  author: 楊以時
  language: lzh
  text: 稻花風際白豆莢雨餘靑物物得其所我歌溪上亭
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 題平陵驛亭
  author: 楊以時
  language: lzh
  text: 稻花風際白。豆莢雨餘靑。物物得其所。我歌溪上亭。
korean:
  title: 제 평릉 역정
  author: 양이시
  language: kor
  text: |-
    벼꽃은 바람 앞에 희고
    콩 꼬투리는 비온 뒤에 푸르다
    물물마다 제 멋을 얻었는데
    나는 시냇가 정자 위에서 노래하네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0220_010_0510&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: On the Pavilion at Pyeongneung Station
  author: Yang Yi-si
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Rice flowers gleam white beneath the wind,
    Bean pods turn green after the rain.
    Each thing finds its perfect place—
    And I sing here in the pavilion by the stream.
  footnotes:
    - Pyeongneung Station (平陵驛) was a rest station along a major travel route in classical Korea, making it a common subject for travelers' poems.
